ACME Bikaner Solar Power Pvt., a
unit of telecommunications tower-equipment provider ACME Tele
Power Ltd., has won a bid to set up a 25 megawatt solar plant in
 India â€™s eastern state of Odisha.  The company has 50 days to sign the agreement with the
state agency, A.K. Choudhury, deputy director, Odisha Renewable
Energy Development Agency, said today in a phone interview. ACME
Bikaner will have 180 days from signing to generating
electricity from the photovoltaic plant, he said.  ACME Bikaner will invest 2 billion rupees ($37 million) to
set up the plant, it said in an e-mailed statement today. The
company was the lowest bidder with a selling price of 7.28
rupees per unit, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
